#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.73"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.73:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.73:0.2"
msgid "7. Migajālavagga "
msgstr "7. With Migajāla "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.73:0.3"
msgid "73. Tatiyachaphassāyatanasutta "
msgstr "73. Six Fields of Contact (3rd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.45, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.73:1.1"
msgid "“Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, anyone who doesn’t truly understand the six fields of contacts’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape "

msgctxt "sn35.73:1.2"
msgid "Avusitaṃ tena brahmacariyaṃ, ārakā so imasmā dhammavinayā”ti. "
msgstr "has not completed the spiritual journey and is far from this teaching and training.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.73:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, one of the mendicants said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn35.73:2.2"
msgid "“etthāhaṃ, bhante, anassasaṃ panassasaṃ. "
msgstr "“Here, sir, I’m lost, truly lost. "

msgctxt "sn35.73:2.3"
msgid "Ahañhi, bhante, channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmī”ti. "
msgstr "For I don’t truly understand the six fields of contacts’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.73:3.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhikkhu, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicant? "

msgctxt "sn35.73:3.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.73:4.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.73:5.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.73:6.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.73:7.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.73:7.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.73:8.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.73:9.1"
msgid "“Sotaṃ … "
msgstr "“Is the ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.73:9.2"
msgid "ghānaṃ … "
msgstr "nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.73:9.3"
msgid "jivhā … "
msgstr "tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.73:9.4"
msgid "kāyo … "
msgstr "body … "

msgctxt "sn35.73:9.5"
msgid "mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti? "
msgstr "mind permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.73:10.1"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.73:11.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.73:12.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.73:13.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.73:13.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.73:14.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn35.73:15.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhu, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, sotasmimpi nibbindati, ghānasmimpi nibbindati, jivhāyapi nibbindati, kāyasmimpi nibbindati, manasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind. "

msgctxt "sn35.73:15.2"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.73:15.3"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.73:15.4"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.73:15.5"
msgid "Migajālavaggo dutiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn35.73:16.1"
msgid "Migajālena dve vuttā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.73:16.2"
msgid "Cattāro ca samiddhinā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.73:16.3"
msgid "Upaseno upavāṇo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.73:16.4"
msgid "Chaphassāyatanikā tayoti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
